{
    "id": "particleutil",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "ParticleUtil",
    "description": "Control particle effects — smoke, sparks, dust, magic. Add a particle system to an object, start and stop it, burst on demand, and set how fast it emits.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/particleutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "particleutil",
        "particles",
        "effects",
        "vfx"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "ColorUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/colorutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "NetworkUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/networkutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "ParticleUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "**Particles** are the little bits that make effects feel alive — smoke, sparks, dust clouds, magic sparkles, fire. A **particle system** is the emitter that produces them. `ParticleUtil` lets you add one to an object and control when and how fast it puffs out particles."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Adding a particle system"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`AddParticleSystem(this)` attaches an emitter to the object. Set up its look in the editor, then control it from script."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "class Campfire",
                "{",
                "    void OnInit()",
                "    {",
                "        ParticleUtil.AddParticleSystem(this);",
                "        ParticleUtil.Start(this);   // start puffing smoke",
                "    }",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Starting and stopping"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Start(this)`", "Begins emitting particles continuously."],
                ["`Stop(this)`", "Stops emitting (existing particles finish their life)."],
                ["`Pause(this)`", "Freezes the effect where it is."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Bursts and emission rate"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "For a one-off puff (an impact, a jump of dust), `Emit` fires a set number of particles instantly. To change a continuous effect's intensity, set its emission rate."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Emit(this, number)`", "Releases `number` particles right now — perfect for a burst on impact."],
                ["`SetEmissionRateOverTime(this, value)`", "How many particles stream out per second (a steady flow like smoke)."],
                ["`SetEmissionRateOverDistance(this, value)`", "How many particles appear as the object **moves** (a trail of dust behind a car)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Puff out 20 particles when the player lands.",
                "void OnLand()",
                "{",
                "    ParticleUtil.Emit(this, 20);",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`AddParticleSystem`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Start`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Stop`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Pause`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`Emit`", "`uniscript, int number`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetEmissionRateOverTime`", "`uniscript, int value`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetEmissionRateOverDistance`", "`uniscript, int value`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Use `Emit` for sudden one-time effects (hits, pickups) and `Start` / `Stop` with an emission rate for ongoing effects (smoke, rain, a magic aura)."
        }
    ]
}
